# Prerequisite Gate — Stop Before You Help

Before running `npx @pacaf/wizard-ux@latest`, `pac` commands, `dotnet tool install`, or any tool that depends on Node.js/.NET/Python, **verify the user has the prerequisites installed**.

## When to gate
- Fresh repo (no `package.json`, no `src/`, no `power.config.json`)
- User says "set up", "run the wizard", "get me started", "new machine"
- A command in this session failed with `command not found` / `is not recognized` / `npx: command not found` / `pac: command not found`

## The check (one at a time, no `&&`)
```bash
node --version
npm --version
git --version
dotnet --version
pac help
```
Windows: `py -V`. macOS/Linux: `python3 --version`.

## If anything fails — STOP

Output:
```
🛑 Prerequisite missing — only you can install this

  ❌ <Tool> — <why needed>
       Install: <official link>
       Verify:  <command>

✅ Already installed: <passing tools>

Why I can't do this for you: installer/admin/PATH — close and reopen the
VS Code terminal after install, then say "ready" and I'll re-check.

Full guide: docs/prerequisite-setup.md
```
Then stop. Do not auto-`winget`/`brew`/`choco`/`apt` — those have their own elevation, proxy, and SSL-inspection failure modes you will end up debugging.

## Windows gotchas
- `python3` → Microsoft Store stub. Test with `py -V`.
- VS Code default terminal often `cmd.exe`. Command Palette → **Terminal: Select Default Profile** → **PowerShell**.
- `pac` lives in `%USERPROFILE%\.dotnet\tools` — restart terminal after `dotnet tool install`.
- `npx` exit code 9009 = Node missing or terminal not restarted.
- Corporate SSL inspection → cert errors on `npm`/`dotnet`/`pip`. Diagnose, do not retry.
- OneDrive Files On-Demand → permission errors. Recommend "Always keep on this device" or move repo.

## macOS gotchas
- First `git --version` triggers Xcode CLT GUI installer (user-only).
- Homebrew on Apple Silicon = `/opt/homebrew`; Intel = `/usr/local`. Must `eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"`.

Full details: `.github/instructions/00-prereq-gate.instructions.md`
